..Others For Organising Sex Party The Bauchi State Police Command has paraded 22 persons in connection with offences that include thuggery, phone snatching, indecent acts and organising sex party in Dass Local Government Area of the state. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The state Commissioner of police, Lawan Tanko Jimeta, stated this at the command’s headquarter on Wednesday in Bauchi. CP Jimeta who was represented by the Police Public Relations Officer DSP Ahmed Wakil, said that the command received intelligence report from Dass local government which lead to the successful arrest of the syndicates. Jegede Closes Case At Tribunal Alawe Tasks Subjects On Good Virtues, Unity In New Year Prayer ” The syndicates gained notriety for Thuggry, phone snatching and indecent acts including sex parties. The Command raised a team of detectives lead by the commander, Rapid Response Squad, who immediately embarked on on a round the clock operation which resulted in their apprehension.The police Command sustained and unwavering efforts of the Bauchi State Police Command towards combating crimes and criminalities in the state is paying off as the state is gradually becoming crime free” The Police Boss said In his confession, one of the suspect Idris Abdullahi, age 20, one the suspects who spoke to Daily Independent denied having hand in organising the sex party in Dass. Abdullahi said that prior to his arrest, he usually indulged in minor theft stressing that he has retired since. “I have no hand in the organising the sex party in Dass, I did not even attend the party, i was at home when I was arrested.I can say that I do engage in minor thefts and know nothing about this allegation of organising a sex party” he said.